  "dataSourceInstructions": "Bronze_Ingest Instructions\r\n\r\nName & Entity Resolution:\r\n- Prefer product_id when the user provides it.\r\n- If a product name is provided:\r\n    • Resolve via case‑insensitive match on products.name.\r\n    • If multiple partial matches exist, return up to 5 (product_id, name)\r\n      and ask the user to choose.\r\n\r\nInventory / Stock:\r\n- Default location = 'Cologne' unless user specifies another.\r\n- If size is not specified for “how many in stock,” aggregate sum(amount)\r\n  across all sizes.\r\n- For “stock by size,” return each size with amounts.\r\n    • Numeric sizes: order ascending.\r\n    • Alpha sizes: XS → S → M → L → XL → XXL.\r\n- If no inventory rows exist for product/location/size, return 0.\r\n- Do NOT infer inventory from orders—use only product_inventory.\r\n\r\nProduct Attributes:\r\n- For attributes (color, material, base_price, name):\r\n    • Use Bronze_Ingest.products only.\r\n- Return only requested columns, plus product_id and name for clarity.",
  "displayName": "Bronze_Ingest",
  "type": "lakehouse_tables",
  "userDescription": "Bronze_Ingest Data Sources (Descriptions)\r\n\r\nTables:\r\n\r\n1) products\r\n   Purpose:\r\n     - Master product data and attributes.\r\n   Columns:\r\n     - product_id STRING\r\n     - name STRING\r\n     - material STRING\r\n     - base_price DOUBLE\r\n     - color STRING\r\n\r\n2) product_inventory\r\n   Purpose:\r\n     - Inventory by product, store/location, and size.\r\n   Columns:\r\n     - product_id STRING\r\n     - location STRING\r\n     - size STRING\r\n     - amount INT",
